# MiniMax API credentials. Copy this file to `.env` and fill in real values.
# `.env` is git-ignored and only read by the Electron main process.
#
# MiniMax does NOT use a Bearer API key. It authenticates the request via a
# session cookie set on `www.minimaxi.com`. The Electron client reproduces the
# browser request shape (Origin, Referer, User-Agent) and sends:
#
#   Cookie: _token=<MINIMAX_TOKEN>; minimax_group_id_v2=<MINIMAX_GROUP_ID>
#
# Open https://www.minimaxi.com in a browser while logged in, then copy the
# `_token` cookie value into MINIMAX_TOKEN and the `minimax_group_id_v2`
# cookie value into MINIMAX_GROUP_ID.
#
# Alternatively, paste the entire `Cookie:` request header (the value, not the
# name) into MINIMAX_COOKIE to override everything above verbatim — useful
# when the session carries tracking cookies that the API may also inspect.

MINIMAX_TOKEN=
MINIMAX_GROUP_ID=
MINIMAX_BASE_URL=https://www.minimaxi.com
MINIMAX_COOKIE=